Heat broiler to high. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash
and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1}. Halve, peel, and
dice @yellow onion{1}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%oz}
into ½-inch cubes.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook until al dente,
~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings),
then drain.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large, preferably
ovenproof, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, stirring,
until just browned, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in onion, garlic, and half the
@Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later). Cook, stirring, until
onion is softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @marinara cup{1%14oz}, penne, remaining Tuscan Heat Spice, and reserved
pasta cooking water to pan with veggies; stir to combine. Let simmer until
warmed through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}
(you'll use the rest later). Season with plenty of salt and pepper.

> TIP: If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer pasta now to a #baking dish{}.

In a small #bowl{}, stir together @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, remaining
Parmesan, and a drizzle of olive oil. Top pasta with mozzarella, then panko
mixture.

Transfer pasta to top rack and broil until panko is golden brown, sauce is
bubbly, and cheese has melted, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly, then divide between plates or bowls. Drizzle with
@basil oil{5%tsp} and serve.